modules.description: This module manages a generation counter and provides functions to wrap values with a generation tag, extract values, and conditionally execute functions based on the current generation. It supports delayed or conditional execution patterns by associating values with a specific generation. Concrete use cases include managing state snapshots and controlling function resumption based on generation changes.

This module manages event channels for interdomain communication in a virtualized environment. It provides operations to create, bind, notify, and close event channels, along with checking their validity. Concrete use cases include setting up event-driven communication between virtual domains or handling domain exception interrupts.
